HEADWORD: Congruent
<hw>Con"gru*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>congruens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>congruere</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>congruent</ets>.]</ety> <def>Possessing congruity; suitable;
agreeing; corresponding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>congruent</qex> and harmonious fitting of parts in a
sentence.</q> <rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Congruent figures</b></col> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>,
<cd>concurring figures.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
